This paper is about a regularization method for convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the method on image classification and object detection tasks, which are subfields of computer vision and machine learning. Additionally, the paper introduces a new form of structured dropout, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze text data, which could be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
